Taita Taveta Governor John Mruttu has asked religious leaders to help fight the rise in rape and sexual abuse.He said that religious, political leaders and the public will hold prayers in Lushangonyi, where cases of defilement, incest, rape and gender-based violence are rampant.Mruttu spoke in Wundanyi town on Tuesday during a meeting by Sauti ya Wanawake. &ldquo;Instead of holding meetings in halls, we now have to meet in Lushangonyi where the problem is. We have to take the prayers there and rebuke the evil there,&rdquo; he said. In Lushangonyi a woman and a child were recently raped and killed in separate incidents. Taita Taveta leads in incest cases at the Coast.